Package spx.av.svr

Provides the SPx AV Server GUI classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SvrPanel.ConnectHandler
    Type for connect/disconnect functions that may be installed using installConnectHandler() function.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Applet
    Applet class.
    ClientsPanel
    AV Server ClientsPanel class, which displays a list of receiving clients together with information from one of the receiving clients.
    ComponentDialog
    ComponentDialog class.
    DistributionPanel
    AV Server DistributionPanel class, which displays network distribution information and controls for a stream.
    EncAacDialog
    AV Server EncAacDialog class, dialog for configuring an AAC audio encoder.
    EncComponentDialog
    AV Server EncComponentDialog class, base class for all encoder configuration dialogs.
    EncMatroxDialog
    AV Server EncMatroxDialog class, dialog for configuring a Matrox encoder.
    EncMFDialog
    AV Server EncMFDialog class, dialog for configuring a Media Foundation encoder.
    EncNvidiaDialog
    AV Server EncNvidiaDialog class, dialog for configuring an Nvidia H.264 encoder.
    EncPanel
    AV Server EncPanel class, a panel for showing encoder information with button to display applicable encoder dialog.
    EncWmaDialog
    AV Server EncWmaDialog class, dialog for configuring an WMA audio encoder.
    EncWmvDialog
    AV Server EncWmvDialog class, dialog for configuring a DMO encoder.
    LatencyPanel
    AV Server LatencyPanel class, a panel for displaying graphs of latency information.
    MainPanel
    MainPanel class, a panel displaying the complete AV server interface that may be used in an application or applet.
    MetadataDialog
    Declares the AV Server MetadataDialog class, a panel for displaying metadata associated with an AV source or process.
    MetadataPanel
    Declares the AV Server MetadataPanel class, a panel for displaying metadata associated with an AV source or process.
    PreviewPanel
    Declares the AV Server PreviewPanel class, a panel for displaying the preview video stream of an AV server stream, if available.
    PriorityPanel
    AV Server PriorityPanel class, a panel for controlling stream priorities.
    RecordDialog
    AV Server RecordDialog class, a dialog for configuring video recording.
    RecordPanel
    AV Server RecordPanel class, a panel for displaying video recording information.
    SrcComponentDialog
    AV Server SrcComponentDialog class, base class for all dialogs that allow the configuration of a source object.
    SrcCondorDialog
    AV Server SrcDShowDialog class, dialog for configuring a Direct Show source.
    SrcDShowDialog
    AV Server SrcDShowDialog class, dialog for configuring a Direct Show source.
    SrcDvpDialog
    AV Server SrcDvpDialog class, dialog for configuring a DVP source.
    SrcFileDialog
    AV Server SrcFileDialog class, dialog for configuring a file source.
    SrcFileMFDialog  
    SrcMatroxDialog
    AV Server SrcMatroxDialog class, dialog for configuring a Matrox source.
    SrcMFDialog
    AV Server SrcMFDialog class, dialog for configuring a Media Foundation source.
    SrcPanel
    AV Server SrcPanel class, a panel for showing source information with button to display applicable source dialog.
    SrcScreenDialog
    AV Server SrcScreenDialog class, dialog for configuring a Screen capture source.
    SrcTestDialog
    AV Server SrcTestDialog class, dialog for configuring a video Test source.
    SrcV4LDialog
    AV Server SrcV4LDialog class, dialog for configuring a Video 4 Linux source.
    StreamComponentPanel
    Declares the AV Server StreamComponentPanel class, base class for all panels that will be contained in a stream panel.
    StreamEncPanel
    AV Server StreamEncPanel class, panel that contains everything for the control of an encode stream.
    StreamPanel
    AV Server StreamPanel class, base class for all stream panels: StreamEncPanel, StreamReplayPanel, and StreamTestPanel.
    StreamReplayPanel
    AV Server StreamReplayPanel class, panel that contains everything for the control of an replay stream.
    StreamsPanel
    AV Server StreamsPanel class, panel that contains all the streams in a tabbed interface.
    StreamTestPanel
    AV Server StreamTestPanel class, panel that contains everything for the control of an test stream.
    SvrConnectPanel
    AV Server SvrConnectPanel class, panel that allows control over which remote AV server is controlled by the GUI.
    SvrHealthPanel
    AV Server SvrHealthPanel class, panel that displays health information from the connected AV server.
    SvrInfoPanel
    AV Server SvrInfoPanel class, panel that displays status information from the connected AV server.
    SvrPanel
    AV Server SvrPanel class, panel that controls connection to an AV server and displays information and controls associated with the currently connected server.
    SvrPriorityPanel
    AV Server SvrPriorityPanel class, panel that allows configuration of server wide priority settings.
    SvrRecordPanel
    AV Server SvrRecordPanel class, panel for control of multi-input recording.
    SvrReplayPanel
    AV Server SvrReplayPanel class, panel for control of multi-output file source.
    SvrSaveConfigPanel
    AV Server SvrSaveConfigPanel class, panel for saving the AV server configuration.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LatencyPanel.Mode
    Modes available for display.
    SrcPanel.StreamType
    Depending on the stream type the SrcPanel will display different information.

Package spx.av.svr Description

Provides the SPx AV Server GUI classes.
